{"sectionId":669,"sectionIdLiteral":"669","humanId":"lesson-254","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"Let every voice but God‚Äôs be still in me.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 254"},"annotation":"W-254","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-254\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"669#1\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, today I would but hear Your Voice.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>In deepest silence I would come to You, to hear Your Voice and to receive Your Word.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>I have no prayer but this: I come to You to ask You for the truth.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>And truth is but Your Will, which I would share with You today.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"669#2\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Today we let no ego thoughts direct our words or actions.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>When such thoughts occur, we quietly step back and look at them, and then we let them go.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>We do not want what they would bring with them.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>And so we do not choose to keep them.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#2:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>They are silent now.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"669#2:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>And in the stillness, hallowed by His Love, God speaks to us and tells us of our will, as we have chosen to remember Him.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Father, today I would but hear Your Voice. In deepest silence I would come to You, to hear Your Voice and to receive Your Word. I have no prayer but this: I come to You